rsonal-finance%2Fbest-retirement-plans%5C%22%3Eretirement%20planning%3C%2Fa%3E%20secret%20I%20didn't%20know%20about%20yet%3F%20But%20the%20more%20I%20looked%20into%20it%2C%20the%20more%20I%20realized%20living%20off%20your%20dividends%20was%20a%20tactic%20that%2C%20while%20requiring%20strategy%20and%20good%20planning%2C%20could%20set%20a%20retiree%20up%20for%20a%20comfortable%20life%20when%20they%20stop%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20does%20it%20mean%20to%20live%20off%20your%20dividends%3F%20If%20you%20invest%20in%20dividend-paying%20stocks%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmutual-funds%5C%22%3Emutual%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20ETFs%2C%20which%20provide%20distributions%20of%20stocks%20or%20cash%20to%20shareholders%2C%20over%20time%2C%20the%20cash%20generated%20by%20those%20dividend%20payments%20can%20supplement%20your%20income%20when%20you%20retire.%20Depending%20on%20how%20much%20money%20you%20have%20in%20those%20stocks%20or%20funds%2C%20their%20growth%20over%20time%2C%20and%20how%20much%20you%20reinvest%20your%20dividends%2C%20you%20could%20be%20generating%20enough%20money%20to%20live%20off%20of%20each%20year%2C%20without%20having%20any%20other%20retirement%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20appeals%20to%20me%20because%20I%20started%20planning%20for%20retirement%20in%20my%2030s.%20Before%20then%2C%20I%20didn't%20put%20any%20cash%20away%20in%20a%20401(k)%20or%20IRA.%20I've%20always%20felt%20behind%20on%20my%20retirement%20savings%20goals%2C%20and%20since%20I%20want%20to%20retire%20in%20my%2050s%2C%20adding%20dividend%20stocks%20and%20funds%20to%20my%20retirement%20plans%20seems%20like%20a%20viable%20option.%20Here's%20how%20I'm%20working%20now%20to%20be%20able%20to%20tap%20into%20dividends%20when%20I%20retire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI'm%20researching%20the%20best%20dividend-paying%20stocks%20and%20funds%20for%20me%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20already%20invest%20in%20a%20few%20dividend-paying%20stocks%20through%20my%20SEP%20IRA%2C%20I%20want%20to%20invest%20in%20individual%20dividend-paying%20stocks%20in%20a%20taxable%20brokerage%20account%20as%20well.%20To%20pick%20the%20right%20stocks%2C%20I%20need%20to%20spend%20time%20researching%20companies%20that%20meet%20my%20criteria%2C%20which%20include%20long-term%20profitability%2C%20solid%20cash%20flow%2C%20and%20a%20track%20record%20of%20dividend%20payouts%20from%20years%20prior.%20Because%20this%20isn't%20my%20expertise%2C%20once%20I%20have%20a%20list%20of%20potential%20stocks%20I'm%20interested%20in%2C%20I%20plan%20to%20consult%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-online-financial-advisors%5C%22%3Efinancial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20advice%20and%20guidance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3EWealthfront%20is%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-robo-advisors%5C%22%3Ebest%20robo-advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20investing%20options%20for%20low-cost%20automated%20or%20self-managed%20portfolios.%20Read%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwealthfront-review%5C%22%3EWealthfront%20investing%20review%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3EI'm%20determining%20how%20much%20I%20want%20this%20to%20make%20up%20my%20retirement%20plan%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20living%20off%20of%20dividend%20checks%20is%20something%20I%20hope%20to%20do%20when%20I%20retire%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20make%20it%20my%20entire%20plan.%20For%20the%20past%20four%20years%2C%20I've%20stuck%20to%20a%20regular%20and%20robust%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fsep-ira%5C%22%3ESEP%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E%20contribution%20plan%20and%20want%20to%20use%20that%20retirement%20fund%20to%20support%20the%20majority%20of%20my%20lifestyle%20when%20I%20stop%20working.%20While%20I%20do%20have%20some%20dividend-generating%20stocks%20in%20my%20SEP%20IRA%20portfolio%2C%20it's%20a%20very%20small%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20what's%20inside%20my%20SEP%20IRA%2C%20I%20want%20to%20continue%20to%20work%20toward%20a%20strategy%20that%20has%20my%20retirement%20plan%20shaping%20up%20to%20include%2020%25%20future%20income%20from%20dividend%20stocks%2C%2030%25%20passive%20income%20from%20real%20estate%20and%20small%20business%20investments%2C%2030%25%20income%20from%20my%20SEP%20IRA%20(including%20some%20dividend%20stocks)%2C%20and%2020%25%20from%20side%20hustles%20that%20I'd%20like%20to%20do%20when%20I%20officially%20retire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI'm%20budgeting%20a%20certain%20amount%20to%20invest%20quarterly%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20on%20a%20strict%20budget%20that%20allows%20me%20to%20contribute%20a%20set%20amount%20of%20cash%20every%20month%20to%20my%20SEP%20IRA.%20Now%2C%20I%20also%20want%20to%20budget%20a%20certain%20amount%20every%20quarter%20to%20invest%20in%20more%20dividend-paying%20stocks%20and%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20this%20isn't%20my%20top%20priority%20right%20now%2C%20I'll%20determine%20how%20much%20to%20invest%20based%20on%20what%20other%20financial%20goals%20I've%20met%20that%20quarter.%20As%20I%20get%20more%20financially%20savvy%20and%20earn%20more%20money%2C%20I%20plan%20to%20increase%20my%20contributions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI'm%20deciding%20how%20much%20of%20the%20dividends%20to%20take%20before%20retirement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20really%20make%20dividend-yielding%20stocks%20a%20worthwhile%20source%20of%20income%20in%20retirement%20is%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20you're%20reinvesting%20the%20distributions%20you%20receive%20to%20buy%20more%20stocks.%20That%20way%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20cash%20you%20have%20in%20that%20stock%20or%20fund%20can%20grow%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20I%20want%20to%20make%20a%20big%20financial%20move%20now%2C%20I%20can%20use%20some%20of%20those%20dividends%20to%20help%20support%20that%20purchase%2C%20and%20the%20distributions%20will%20be%20taxed%20as%20income.%20I'v