the%20monarch's%20role%20as%20the%20head%20of%20state%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20his%20royal%20lineage%2C%20and%20his%20personal%20passions.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20look%20at%20some%20details%20that%20are%20easy%20to%20miss%20at%20first%20glance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECharles'%20bright%20red%20uniform%20is%20from%20the%20Welsh%20Guards%2C%20a%20regiment%20of%20the%20British%20army.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22King%20Charles%20III%20wearing%20a%20red%20military%20uniform%20and%20a%20royal%20guard%20hat%20while%20riding%20a%20horse.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66439c34f27898f532d77c3a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221980%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECharles%2C%20then%20known%20as%20Prince%20Charles%2C%20took%20part%20in%20Trooping%20the%20Colour%20in%20June%201976.%3Cp%3EAnwar%20Hussein%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECharles%20is%20depicted%20holding%20a%20sword%20and%20wearing%20the%20ruby-red%20signature%20uniform%20of%20the%20Welsh%20Guards%2C%20a%20regiment%20of%20the%20British%20army%20that%20he%20was%20named%20Regimental%20Colonel%20of%20in%201975.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20king%20has%20worn%20the%20uniform%20during%20the%20annual%20Trooping%20the%20Colour%20ceremony%2C%20which%20honors%20the%20monarch's%20birthday%20at%20the%20Horse%20Guards%20Parade%20in%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20red%20in%20the%20uniform%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20painting%20is%20a%20nod%20to%20Charles'%20%26quot%3Broyal%20heritage%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20color%20often%20appears%20in%20many%20historical%20royal%20paintings%2C%20according%20to%20Yeo's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jonathanyeo.com%2Fnew-index-41%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20he%20offered%20further%20insights%20into%20his%20artistic%20choices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHis%20uniform%20fades%20into%20the%20background%20of%20the%20red-painted%20canvas%20on%20purpose.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22British%20artist%20Jonathan%20Yeo%2C%20wearing%20a%20blue%20suit%20and%20dark-rimmed%20glasses%2C%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20the%20portrait%20he%20painted%20of%20King%20Charles%20III%20at%20Buckingham%20Palace.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66439cac9686a6f37bffbd54%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EArtist%20Jonathan%20Yeo%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20his%20official%20portrait%20of%20Britain's%20King%20Charles%20III%20on%20May%2014.%3Cp%3EAARON%20CHOWN%2FPOOL%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYeo%20also%20explained%20on%20his%20website%20that%20Charles'%20red%20uniform%20purposefully%20blends%20into%20the%20swirls%20of%20red%20paint%20that%20cover%20most%20of%20the%20canvas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20chose%20to%20fade%20the%20uniform%20out%20and%20keep%20Charles'%20face%20more%20pronounced%20to%20allow%20viewers%20to%20feel%20a%20sense%20of%20connection%20with%20the%20king%20as%20a%20person%20rather%20than%20have%20their%20attention%20diverted%20by%20his%20regalia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20portrait%20artist%2C%20you%20get%20this%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20spend%20time%20with%20and%20get%20to%20know%20a%20subject%2C%20so%20I%20wanted%20to%20minimise%20the%20visual%20distractions%20and%20allow%20people%20to%20connect%20with%20the%20human%20being%20underneath%2C%26quot%3B%20Yeo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20butterfly%20next%20to%20Charles'%20shoulder%20is%20thought%20to%20have%20been%20named%20after%20another%20British%20ruler.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Many%20believe%20monarch%20butterflies%20were%20named%20after%20William%20III%2C%20popularly%20known%20as%20William%20of%20Orange.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66439f1eb4abc992e8c9624c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22