a%20few.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Krystelle%20Dsouza%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F349417%2Fifs-officer-sanjeev-chaturvedi-uttarakhand-endangered-plants-conservation-patwa-gentiana-lilium-polyphyllum%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98How%20I%20Got%20a%20Job%20At%20NASA%E2%80%99%3A%20Aerospace%20Engineer%20Shares%205%20Tips%20to%20Build%20a%20Career%20in%20Space%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAkshata%20Krishnamurthy%E2%80%99s%20fascination%20with%20space%20began%20as%20a%20child%20as%20she%20wondered%20about%20what%20lies%20beyond%20our%20planet.%20Her%20curiosity%20was%20fuelled%20by%20weekly%20visits%20to%20the%20planetariums%20and%20air%20shows%20in%20Bengaluru.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20no%20surprise%20then%20that%20this%20young%20girl%20would%20want%20to%20pursue%20a%20career%20in%20aerospace.%20But%20how%2C%20where%2C%20and%20what%20to%20do%20to%20achieve%20this%20dream%20was%20a%20path%20she%20had%20to%20navigate%20on%20her%20own.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20incredible%20talent%20and%20a%20dogged%20pursuit%20of%20her%20goal%2C%20she%20became%20a%20student%20at%20the%20Massachusetts%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20(MIT)%2C%20which%20was%20a%20huge%20deal%20for%20the%20student%20who%20studied%20in%20a%20state%20board%20school%20and%20came%20from%20a%20middle%20class%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20this%20gritty%20woman%20works%20as%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F324699%2Fawais-ahmed-founded-space-startup-pixxel-hyperspectral-satellite-launch-hyperloop-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaerospace%20engineer%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20National%20Aeronautics%20and%20Space%20Administration%20(NASA).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20her%20journey%20was%20not%20an%20easy%20one.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavigating%20through%20the%20various%20hurdles%20of%20having%20an%20education%20abroad%20to%20setting%20foot%20at%20NASA%20as%20a%20full-time%20employee%20took%20her%20almost%2015%20years.%20But%20this%2035-year-old%20is%20making%20it%20easy%20for%20others%20by%20sharing%20her%20experiences%20on%20social%20media%2C%20and%20mentoring%20them.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20her%20story.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EIn%20pursuit%20of%20the%20universe%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkshata%20works%20as%20a%20Principal%20Investigator%20and%20Space%20Systems%20Engineer%20at%20NASA%20Jet%20Propulsion%20Laboratory%20(JPL)%20on%20two%20space%20missions.%20She%20is%20the%20mission%20science%20phase%20lead%20on%20the%20NASA-ISRO%20Synthetic%20Aperture%20Radar%20mission%20(NISAR)%20and%20robotics%20systems%20engineer%20on%20the%20MARS%202020%20Perseverance%20rover%2C%20operating%20the%20rover%20on%20MARS.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20lifelong%20tryst%20with%20space%20took%20roots%20at%20an%20airshow%20in%20Bengaluru%20in%202003.%20It%20was%20the%20Aero%20India%20show%20at%20the%20Yelahanka%20air%20force%20base%20that%20perhaps%20started%20it%20all.%20The%20aerobatic%20manoeuvres%20of%20the%20Sukhoi%20Su-30%20pilots%20left%20the%20youngster%20captivated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed%20wp-block-embed-youtube%20wp-embed-aspect-16-9%20wp-has-aspect-ratio%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-embed__wrapper%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FFwPOzvr0oxQ%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22C0159%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22281%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20always%20interested%20in%20science%20and%20maths%20and%20wanted%20to%20know%20more%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F319013%2Fiit-madras-graduates-startup-agnikul-cosmos-manufactures-3d-printed-rockets-video%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorigins%20of%20our%20universe%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20wanted%20to%20know%20more%20about%20where%20we%20come%20from%2C%20and%20what%20is%20out%20there%20in%20the%20sky.%20I%20also%20wanted%20to%20travel%20around%20and%20explore%20but%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20resources%20for%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20Akshata%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDetermined%2C%20she%20fueled%20her%20curiosity%20with%20whatever%20source%20she%20had%20access%20to%2C%20like%20visiting%20the%20local%20factories%20in%20her%20native%20Karnataka%20village%20or%20visiting%20the%20planetariums.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalling%20herself%20an%20%E2%80%98explorer%E2%80%99%2C%20Akshata%20would%20find%20joy%20in%20understanding%20the%20hows%20and%20whys%20of%20everything%20she%20laid%20eyes%20upon.%20This%20sense%20of%20reasoning%20helped%20her%20when%20she%20pursued%20engineering%20later.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20major%20turning%20point%20in%20her%20life%20was%20reading%20about%20the%20Hubble%20Space%20telescope%20which%20ignited%20her%20passion%20for%20aerospace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20watching%20astronauts%20perform%20spacewalks%20while%20servicing%20the%20Hubble%20telescope%20was%20a%20huge%20inspiration.%20It%20made%20me%20dream%20of%20looking%20at%20Earth%20from%20the%20vast%20reaches%20of%20space%20and%20experiencing%20what%20they%20experienced%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20the%20rocket%20scientist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECarving%20her%20own%20path%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20wanted%20to%20become%20an%20astronaut%20and%20that%20was%20a%20clear%20goal%20in%20my%20mind%2C%E2%80%9D%20recalls%20Akshata.%20In%20the%2090s%2C%20she%20knew%20of%20Rakesh%20Sharma%2C%20Kalpana%20Chawla%20and%20Sunita%20Williams.%20While%20Sharma%20was%20in%20the%20Indian%20air%20force%2C%20the%20other%2